Package edu.cmu.cs214.hw5.framework.core.plugin.api

Interface DataPlugin

  • public interface DataPlugin
    This interface specifies the functionality which a data source plugin must provide to service the framework. The core use of a DataPlugin is to retrieve time-series data from some source and convert it to a RawDataSet which can be used by the framework. Data sources contain time-series data associated with individual countries.

    If an API key is required for the plugin to be used, the plugin should specify a required parameter for the key.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the plugin. This method is used by the framework to display the name of the plugin in the menu. The name of the plugin should reflect the source of data used.

        Note that the name of the plugin does not have to be unique from other plugins which may be present in the framework. However, identically named plugins will cause confusion for the user of the framework application, so it is recommended that plugin makers try to avoid potential name collisions (for example, by including a team name in the name of the plugin).

        Returns:
        the name of the plugin as it should appear in the framework menu.

      • getRequiredParameterNames

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> getRequiredParameterNames()
        Returns a list where each element is the name of a parameter to the plugin.

        Example parameter names could be "Start Year" or "Source File Path". If no parameters are required, an empty list should be returned.

        Returns:
        a list of the names of all parameters for the plugin.

      • setParameters

        boolean setParameters​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> parameters)
        Attempt to set the parameters of the plugin using a map from parameter names to parameters.

        The keys of the parameter map should be names of parameters, identical to those returned by the getRequiredParameterNames() function. The value associated with each parameter name key is the intended value for that parameter to be set to, in String form.

        The function should validate the input and ensure that the values for the parameters do not violate any potential constraints. For instance, the value for a "Start Year" parameter should not exceed the value for an "End Year" parameter. If there is any issue with the input parameters, the function should return false. Otherwise, the plugins parameters should be set to the input values, and the function should return true.

        Parameters:
        parameters - a map where the keys are parameter names and the values are parameter values (as Strings).
        Returns:
        true if the parameters are valid, false otherwise.

      • getData

        RawDataSet getData()
        Return the data from the plugin source as a RawDataSet.

        This method will only be called after a set of valid parameters have been provided to the plugin, i.e. that setParameters(Map) has been called and most recently returned true.

        Returns:
        the RawDataSet obtained by the plugin given its previously set parameters.
